snippet.textDisplay: What a beautiful song indeed. Loved it. Listened to it 2 minutes after it was uploaded. Already played 50 times on repeat:) My favorite part started at 2:55 till end with the plateau starting at 3:07 and climaxing at 3:15 and 3:52 when Sajjad Ali touched some great notes (though very shortly). The only thing I'd have loved more was Sajjad Ali singing through all the notes of a raag at some point in the song. He is the maestro and we wait for such notes which not everyone can sign. Great singing by Farheen whom I had not heard before. Excellent work by Coke Studio.

Simple and heartening tunes with seemingly nothing out of the ordinary ! 
Yet it grows on you till at one point your eyes have welled up and you are smiling at the same time ❤

Ended too soon tho.
